Domain: "machine-learning"

Existing knowledge (do not repeat):
- Transfer learning enables adaptation with minimal fine-tuning via frozen lower layers
- LoRA decomposes weight updates into low-rank matrices (rank 4-64), achieving comparable performance with 10-100x fewer parameters
- Attention mechanisms in transformers compute O(n²) pairwise token interactions
- RLHF aligns model outputs with human preferences but introduces reward hacking risks

Open research questions:
- How do scaling laws change when retrieval augmentation supplements model parameters?
- At what point does fine-tuning a small model become more cost-effective than prompting a large one?